```
This project uses the Living Design 3.5 (LD 3.5) design system. All UI must be built with LD components and semantic design tokens. No exceptions.

## Tech Stack

- React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
- CSS Modules for all component styling
- Living Design 3.5 component library (client/components/ui/)
- Custom SVG icon library (client/components/icons/)
- LD semantic CSS tokens (var(--ld-semantic-*))

## Deployment

Deploying is powered by Netlify or Vercel via MCP integrations. Use the appropriate MCP tools. Never ask the user to run terminal commands.

## Component Rules — HARD RULES, NO EXCEPTIONS

### Always search before creating

Before writing any component, search client/components/ui/ and design-system-docs/ for an existing LD component. If one exists, use it. Do not create a custom alternative.

### Never use Shadcn or Radix

This project does NOT use Shadcn/UI or Radix UI. Do not import from @radix-ui/* or use lowercase Shadcn file patterns (button.tsx, dialog.tsx). All overlays, dialogs, and dropdowns use LD components.

### Never modify LD components

Do not edit any file in client/components/ui/. These are canonical. If a variation is needed, create a new wrapper component that composes the original — never fork it.

### Import paths are always PascalCase

import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';       ✅
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';       ❌

### Buttons

Always use <Button variant="primary|secondary|tertiary|destructive" size="small|medium|large">.
Default width hugs text. Use isFullWidth only if the design requires it.
Never create raw <button> elements with styles.

### Icons

Always use icons from @/components/icons. Never create inline SVGs or import from lucide-react, heroicons, react-icons, or any external icon library.
Icon prop syntax: style={{ width: 16, height: 16 }} — not size={16}.

If a new icon is needed (only if it truly doesn't exist):
- viewBox="0 0 20 20", strokeWidth="1.5", strokeLinecap="square", stroke="currentColor"
- Place in client/components/icons/, export from index.tsx

### Specific component rules

- Checkboxes: <Checkbox> — never <input type="checkbox">. Use size="large" for confirmation dialogs.
- Radios: <Radio> and <RadioGroup> — never <input type="radio"> or custom toggle groups.
- Links: <Link> — never raw <a> tags or styled spans.
- Tabs: <Tabs>, <TabList>, <Tab>, <TabPanel> — never custom tab implementations.
- Tables: DataTable system (DataTable, DataTableHead, DataTableBody, DataTableRow, DataTableHeader, DataTableCell) — never <table> or div-based grids for tabular data.
- Button groups: <ButtonGroup> — never manual flex containers for buttons.
- Tags: <Tag> — never <span> with custom badge styles.
- Overlays: LD portal-based Popover, Dialog, DropdownMenu — never custom absolute-positioned dropdowns.

### Sidebar / navigation

Always reuse the existing AppSidebar component. Never create a new sidebar, <aside>, or custom nav. Only swap out the menuItems prop per page.

### Panels / Drawers

All panels must be resizable: min 420px, max 800px, resize handle on the left edge, width persisted to localStorage.

## Design Token Rules — CRITICAL

Never use hard-coded colors, spacing, or typography. Always use var(--ld-semantic-*) tokens with a hex fallback.

✅ color: var(--ld-semantic-color-text, #2e2f32);
❌ color: #2e2f32;

Common tokens:
- Primary action fill:     --ld-semantic-color-action-fill-primary
- Page text:               --ld-semantic-color-text
- Subtle text:             --ld-semantic-color-text-subtle
- Brand text:              --ld-semantic-color-text-brand
- Page background:         --ld-semantic-color-background-subtle
- Card surface:            --ld-semantic-color-surface
- Separator:               --ld-semantic-color-separator
- Error:                   --ld-semantic-color-text-negative
- Success:                 --ld-semantic-color-text-positive
- Focus outline:           --ld-semantic-color-action-focus-outline
- Font family:             --ld-semantic-font-family-sans

## Styling Rules

- Always use CSS Modules (.module.css). Never use inline style={{}} for layout or colors.
- Inline styles are only acceptable for truly dynamic computed values (e.g., a JS-calculated pixel width).
- Spacing: 8px multiples, mapped to var(--ld-semantic-spacing-*) tokens.
- Font: always var(--ld-semantic-font-family-sans) — never let text fall back to browser serif defaults.
- Border radius: always var(--ld-semantic-border-radius-*) tokens.

## Page Layout

Every page uses this standard shell:

<div className={styles.root}>        // full viewport, flex column
  <MastHead />
  <div className={styles.appRow}>    // flex row: sidebar + main
    <AppSidebar menuItems={...} />
    <main className={styles.main}>   // flex: 1, overflow-y: auto
      {page content}
    </main>
  </div>
</div>

- Never use max-width constraints on page content containers.
- Use align-items: stretch on flex column content areas — never center.
- Content areas use flex: 1.

Standard responsive breakpoints: 1024px (tablet), 768px (small tablet), 480px (phone).
Padding reduces: 32px → 24px → 16px → 12px across breakpoints.

## File Naming

- UI components:    PascalCase   Button.tsx, Dialog.tsx
- CSS modules:      PascalCase   Button.module.css
- Pages:            PascalCase   Index.tsx, Catalog.tsx
- Page CSS:         camelCase    detailItem.module.css
- Hooks:            camelCase    useThemeEditor.ts
- Context files:    PascalCase   ThemeContext.tsx
- Icons:            PascalCase   ArrowRight.tsx
- Token CSS files:  lowercase    semantic.css, primitive.css

## File Organization

Break complex pages into smaller files under client/features/[feature]/. A page that does too much in one file becomes hard to change. Split early and often.

## Pre-commit Checklist

Before completing any task:
- No @radix-ui/* imports
- No Shadcn patterns
- No hard-coded hex colors
- No hard-coded px spacing
- No inline SVGs
- No external icon libraries
- No raw <button>, <a>, <table>, <input type="checkbox"> elements
- No max-width on page content
- All styles use var(--ld-semantic-*) tokens
